 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.10","title":"[audit][encoding] Reject source blocks above RFC systematic K limit before repair emission","description":"bv robot triage still ranks the active audit frontier highest, and the remaining clean slice in batch 331 is src/encoding.rs. EncodingPipeline::plan_blocks() currently only enforces the byte-based 256-block cap. With small symbol sizes and large max_block_size values, it can admit a block whose K = ceil(len / symbol_size) exceeds the RFC/systematic encoder maximum 56403. The first repair symbol later goes through SystematicEncoder::new() -> SystematicParams::for_source_block() and panics (or at best fails too late) instead of rejecting the block up front. Scope: make block planning fail closed before any symbol emission, add focused regressions, and validate with rch-backed cargo checks/tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteSnow","created_at":"2026-03-14T04:28:12.779632799Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T05:01:01.860403064Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T05:01:01.860380422Z","close_reason":"Completed: reject source blocks above RFC systematic K limit before emission and preserve sender invalid-params error kind","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.10","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T04:28:12.779632799Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.11","title":"[audit][reactor] Deep audit src/reactor/kqueue.rs registration, wakeup, and close semantics","description":"Focused audit child under asupersync-1qfd0.331 for src/reactor/kqueue.rs only. Scope: inspect registration/update/removal semantics, one-shot/edge-triggered behavior, wakeup/timeout handling, fd lifecycle and close semantics, and fail-closed behavior around stale registrations. Patch any concrete bug with focused regressions and validate with rch-backed cargo gates, or close as SOUND with evidence if the file holds up.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"EmeraldForge","created_at":"2026-03-14T04:33:34.032791714Z","created_by":"EmeraldForge","updated_at":"2026-03-14T04:42:50.197347486Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T04:42:50.197329002Z","close_reason":"Completed; preserved kqueue deregister bookkeeping across hard delete failures with deterministic retry regression","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","kqueue","reactor"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.11","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T04:33:34.032791714Z","created_by":"EmeraldForge","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.12","title":"[audit][dns] Resolver ignores configured nameservers and preset DNS servers","description":"Focused audit child under asupersync-1qfd0.331 for src/net/dns/resolver.rs only. ResolverConfig.nameservers and the ResolverConfig::google()/cloudflare() presets currently promise explicit resolver selection, but the actual lookup path uses std::net::ToSocketAddrs via query_ip_sync() and never consults config.nameservers. Scope: either implement explicit nameserver usage for Phase-0 lookups or fail closed/document the unsupported path so the API no longer silently lies, add focused regressions, and validate via rch-backed cargo gates.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FoggyTower","created_at":"2026-03-14T19:43:54.145570014Z","created_by":"FoggyTower","updated_at":"2026-03-14T19:43:54.145570014Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.12","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T19:43:54.145570014Z","created_by":"FoggyTower","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.13","title":"[audit][lab] Deep audit src/lab/chaos.rs injection, timing, and stats semantics","description":"Focused audit child under asupersync-1qfd0.331 for src/lab/chaos.rs only. Scope: inspect chaos-action scheduling, delayed injection timing, per-action stats accounting, determinism/replay behavior, and fail-closed handling of invalid or overlapping injection plans. Patch any concrete bug with focused regressions and validate via rch-backed cargo gates, or close as SOUND with evidence if the file holds up.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"LavenderFalcon","created_at":"2026-03-14T19:45:36.407025441Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T19:45:36.407025441Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","chaos","lab"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.13","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T19:45:36.407025441Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.2","title":"[audit][grpc] Keep shared service health registered until last HealthReporter drops","description":"Audit follow-up in src/grpc/health.rs. HealthReporter currently clears its service status unconditionally on Drop. If multiple HealthReporter instances exist for the same service, dropping any one of them removes the shared registration even while another reporter for that same service is still alive and may still be marking it serving/not-serving. Scope: retain per-service reporter ownership so only the final reporter drop clears status, add focused regression coverage for multi-reporter lifecycle semantics, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldForge","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:23:31.116168820Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:39:02.938626779Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:39:02.938585803Z","close_reason":"Fixed grpc/health multi-reporter lifecycle bug; added regression; targeted remote test and remote cargo check passed; fmt check passed; remote clippy blocked by rch instability","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:23:31.116168820Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
