 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.4","title":"[audit][dns] Preserve timeout classification in happy_eyeballs_connect","description":"Audit follow-up in src/net/dns/resolver.rs. Resolver::happy_eyeballs_connect() currently maps every io::Error from happy-eyeballs racing into DnsError::Connection(e.to_string()). That collapses timeout outcomes into generic connection errors, diverging from both the resolver timeout contract and the sequential connect path, which returns DnsError::Timeout. Scope: preserve timeout classification for happy-eyeballs connect failures, add a deterministic regression using the zero-timeout path, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldForge","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:06:14.701285747Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T03:17:08.919551065Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T03:17:08.919527562Z","close_reason":"Completed: preserved happy-eyeballs timeout classification; added zero-timeout regression","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.331","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:06:14.701285747Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
